<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-63-0908 </DOCNO><TEXT>In this era of a mixed-market supply of energy generation, there are qualifyingfacilities and cogeneration alternatives compensated at a market based``avoided cost,'' and traditional utility generation (baseload, intermediate,and peaking units) compensated at the utility's authorized rate of return,there needs to be consideration given to ratemaking treatments that willprovide incentives to utilities to take the risk of investing in a (baseload)project that is expected to provide significant fuel savings.</TEXT></DOC>